rComments: Really great prof ! If you have the chance to take just do it ! He's so supportive with his students and does everything to help them

An Amazing professor! He wants his students to exceed. His assignments were very well explained in class and the midterm was quite easy if you pay attention to his lectures. Overall, a great professor! Would take his class again.

He's super nice but unprofessional. Will not respond to emails and you must message him through MS teams to maybe get a reply. Says he'll release grades, but then doesn't until very late. Says the quizzes are tested only from his slides, but to do well you MUST read the textbook. Overall nice guy, just frustrating when you can't take his word.
One of my favorite professors. You can tell that he wants his students to do good in this course.

He is a good guy BUT He is making easy course to hard one. Didn't ask any questions from the textbook or slides, so what was the use of getting the textbook if he wasn't going to use it. Lost so many points for quizzes and exams because he made it unnecessarily hard. Didn't respond to any of the emails, take another professor if you have a choice.

Not a big fan of this professor because he takes too long to release the grades of assignments and quizzes, causing others to postpone their decision on whether or not to drop the course. Plus, his quizzes are difficult; quizzes should be easy marks and should ask questions directly from the slide, but they are not.
Excellent Prof. Knows his material well.
I really learnt a lot from his class particularly Excel. Hes very flexible and gives you extension to submit your assignment without any stress.
He is a good person, but grade so hard
Amazing Prof. Very friendly and understanding. Really enjoyed his class.
AMAZING prof.! Put in the effort and you'll do great!
Top class Prof. Really learnt a lot from this guy. His class inspired me to change my major to BTM.
The Prof is good but his TA was a tough grader. Highly recommend for MIS students.
Awesome Prof! One of the best at teaching online. Class was always fun and engaging.
Literally the best and most understanding professor ever. He's a really good teacher and accessible outside of class. Assignments are easy, exams are fair. He's so cool!!
His exams are very straight forward and are based on class discussion and tutorials. His exam was open book which was amazing but you need to study to know where all the contents are.
Although the class was from 7 to 10pm, I looked forward to it every week. He is so chilled and flexible and very understanding of student workloads.
Not a very good teacher and confusing as to what you need to know for tests. Class is relatively easy tho

Professor Ohiomah was a great teacher & I hope to have him again in the future for a different class. He's chill & understanding & easy to talk to, and helpful. & I learned alot of useful info from this class.

Great Professor. He does the MOST to ensure you have everything you need to succeed and is very helpful when you reach out to him. He is more than fair in every deliverable that is graded and gives you a lot of time to complete the assignments. If you are willing to put in the work and attend class you should have absolutely no problem.
He is so easy going and genuinely cares about student workloads.
Amazing professor, amazing personality and really helpful/friendly with his fellow students. He is probably the most approachable professor i've seen

Although the deliverable structure expectation seemed to shift a bit, the professor made the content (that could have been very dry) an engaging experience. Alhassan often used our classes research topics (which shows he remembered our work inprogress) to relate it the course matter.

Professor Alhassan Ohiomah knows the subject very well and his teaching style is excellent. He helps in every confusion related to the subject and is available to answer any doubts afterclass hours too.
Hilarious teacher, good course. I learned a lot about technology and its reaction to business and the applications as well.

The prof for this course is extremely understanding. He would sometimes postpone an assignment during midterms for example and I really appreciate that. He is a very nice person as well as a prof and would always come to class prepared.
By far the most understanding Prof at the Telfer School of Management. He's very flexible and gets student feedback for components of the course.
Good guy and very flexible with assignment deadlines

This Professor has unrealistic expectations for his student it's almost like he doesn't realize that we have other classes. You will have 7 days between each group case study and he even gives you the midterm 2 days before a group case is due.

Professor Ohiomah is a great teacher who is passionate about the applications of technology in business. His lectures are wellstructured. He's very accessible outside of class if students were to have any questions.

The prof for this course is extremely understanding. He would sometimes postpone an assignment during midterms for example and I really appreciate that. He is a very nice person as well as a prof and would always come to class prepared
Professor is extremely understanding of student's schedules and ensures that what is best for us is what happens. Overall an excellent teacher that puts the students first.

Changes assignments' deadline multiple times without any notice, requires students to purchase access codes that completely useless, can't teach properly. Need to attend 80% of the class in in order to be eligible to write the exam. Avoid at all costs!!!
Really nice and chill. Class consisted of case studies and final.
The Professor knows the subject very well and knows how to teach. He is very open and communicates clearly with students. I hope to take a class with him again in the future.

Pretty straightforward prof. This class isn't difficult if you go over notes and go to your labs. It is easy to fall behind, but it isn't too hard to catch up either. Purchased the e-textbook but barely used it.
